# Volume storage

Keep everything for this project on `/Volumes/JohnDovey` as much as possible:

- Use `/Volumes/JohnDovey/tmp` for temporary/scratch files that should persist, not the
  internal disk's `/tmp`.
- Go build/module caches should also live on the volume, not the default `~/go` or
  `~/Library/Caches`.
- Precedent: sibling projects (ClonesApp, WalkieTalkie) redirect
  `GOPATH`/`GOCACHE`/`GOMODCACHE`/`TMPDIR` **per-project via env vars in that project's own
  build/run scripts** (e.g. `/Volumes/JohnDovey/tmp/walkietalkie-gopath`) rather than editing
  the global `go env` or shell rc. Global `go env` intentionally still points at the default
  `~/go` — don't change that globally.

Once this project has Go tooling wired up, create a project-scoped cache dir under
`/Volumes/JohnDovey/tmp/lansync-*` and export `GOPATH`/`GOCACHE`/`GOMODCACHE`/`TMPDIR` for it
in this project's own scripts (e.g. a `tools/go-env.sh` following WalkieTalkie's pattern).
